### Elasticsearch Version

serverless

### Installed Plugins

_No response_

### Java Version

_bundled_

### OS Version

N/A

### Problem Description

When the first document is stored in an index that leverages a semantic_text field, information is retrieved from the inference API and persisted in the index mapping. This includes fields like the `dimensions`, `task_type`.

Currently the endpoint metadata is persisted in the index mapping. The metadata isn't used by the semantic text field after an inference id is chosen and the information may confuse the user. It can also be out of date with what the inference API exposes through its REST GET API.

We should filter out the endpoint metadata so it isn't stored in the index mappings.

### Steps to Reproduce

1. Create an index

```
PUT my-index
{
    "mappings": {
        "properties": {
            "my_field": {
                "type": "semantic_text",
                "inference_id": ".google-gemini-embedding-001"
            }
        }
    }
}
```

2. Ingest a document
```
POST my-index/_doc/1
{
    "my_field": "hello"
}
```

3. The metadata field will show up in the index mapping:

```
{
  "my-index": {
    "aliases": {},
    "mappings": {
      "properties": {
        "my_field": {
          "type": "semantic_text",
          "inference_id": ".google-gemini-embedding-001",
          "model_settings": {
            "service": "elastic",
            "task_type": "text_embedding",
            "dimensions": 3072,
            "similarity": "cosine",
            "element_type": "float",
            "metadata": {
              "heuristics": {
                "properties": [
                  "multilingual"
                ],
                "status": "ga",
                "release_date": "2025-07-14"
              },
              "internal": {
                "fingerprint": "fb3e18481f118e3d3883669be08b9637ac235f8efd2b4f4ec2035b1478878bbd",
                "version": 1
              },
              "display": {
                "name": "Google Gemini Embedding v1",
                "model_creator": "Google"
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "settings": {}
  }
}
```

